WHO   — The Color Pie — the WUBRG wheel · the design soul
WHAT  — Magic's central design philosophy (codified by Mark Rosewater): five complete, defensible worldviews, none good or evil, balanced against each other.
WHERE — MTG · MTG Arena  Framework inputs: Magic: The Gathering / MTG Arena (WotC)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the whole game's depth and identity rest here — and the wheel is so true that people use WUBRG to read personalities.
HOW   — By a five-fold balance of values and mechanics, kept rigorous across thirty years of design.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Five answers to one question, allied and opposed in a ring — no colour is the good one, which is exactly why the wheel can sort a soul.

